recalls.Summary: Toyota Motor Engineering & Manufacturing (Toyota) is recalling certain 2022-2026 Toyota, Lexus, and Subaru Solterra vehicles equipped with a Panoramic View Monitor (PVM) system. Please see the recall report for a complete list of models. A software error may cause the rearview camera to freeze or display a blank screen when the vehicle is in reverse. As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 111, "Rear Visibility."
recalls.Consequence: A rearview camera that fails to display an image can reduce the driver's view behind the vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the parking assist software, free of charge. Owner letters were mailed January 2, 2026. Owners may contact Toyota's customer service at 1-800-331-4331. Toyota's numbers for this recall are 25TB13 and 25LB06. Subaru's number for this recall is WRE25.

recalls.Summary: Toyota Motor Engineering & Manufacturing (Toyota) is recalling certain 2022-2024 Toyota Tundra, Lexus LX, and 2024 Lexus GX vehicles equipped with a V35A engine. Debris from the manufacturing process may contaminate the engine and cause the main bearings to fail, which can result in an engine stall and loss of drive power.
recalls.Consequence: A loss of drive power increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: The remedy is currently under development. Once the repair is available, repairs will be performed free of charge. Interim letters notifying owners of the safety risk were mailed December 16, 2025. Additional letters will be sent once the final remedy is available. Owners may contact Toyota's customer service at 1-800-331-4331. Toyota's numbers for this recall are 25TB14 and 25TA14. Lexus' numbers for this recall are 25LB07 and 25LA07. This recall expands previous NHTSA recall number 24V381.

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Unresponsive
issues.description: Multiple owners report the infotainment system becoming unresponsive, freezing on startup, or experiencing significant lag during operation. The 14-inch touchscreen may display a black screen or become completely non-functional.
issues.fix_description: Software update from dealership, system reset, or in severe cases, complete infotainment module replacement
issues.prevention: Regular software updates and avoid rapid temperature changes in the vehicle

issues.title: Paint Quality Issues and Premature Chipping
issues.description: Several owners have reported paint quality issues including premature chipping, particularly on the front bumper and hood areas. Some report paint appearing thin or easily damaged by road debris.
issues.fix_description: Touch-up paint for minor chips, or professional repainting for larger areas
issues.prevention: Apply paint protection film, avoid following closely behind vehicles, regular washing

issues.title: Air Suspension Calibration Problems
issues.description: Some owners experience issues with the air suspension system not properly calibrating or maintaining ride height. The system may display warning messages or fail to adjust to different drive modes.
issues.fix_description: System recalibration, sensor replacement, or air strut replacement if damaged
issues.prevention: Regular maintenance, avoid extreme off-road conditions during break-in period

issues.title: Hybrid System Error Messages
issues.description: Reports of hybrid system throwing error codes and warning messages, sometimes resulting in reduced power or entering limp mode. Issues may be related to software calibration or sensor malfunctions.
issues.fix_description: Software update, sensor replacement, or hybrid battery system diagnosis and repair
issues.prevention: Regular maintenance, proper break-in procedures, software updates

issues.title: Door Handle and Electronic Access Issues
issues.description: Some owners report problems with electronic door handles not responding properly or keyless entry system malfunctioning. Handles may not extend or retract correctly.
issues.fix_description: Handle mechanism cleaning/lubrication, actuator replacement, or electronic module reprogramming
issues.prevention: Regular cleaning, avoid forcing handles, keep key fob battery fresh

issues.title: Climate Control Temperature Inconsistency
issues.description: Reports of climate control system not maintaining consistent temperatures or having difficulty reaching set temperature. Some zones may blow different temperature air than selected.
issues.fix_description: System calibration, actuator replacement, or refrigerant service
issues.prevention: Regular cabin air filter replacement, system maintenance checks

issues.title: Fuel Economy Lower Than EPA Estimates
issues.description: Multiple owners report real-world fuel economy significantly lower than EPA estimates, particularly in city driving conditions. The hybrid system may not be optimizing as expected.
issues.fix_description: Software update, driving habit adjustment, or system calibration
issues.prevention: Proper break-in period, efficient driving techniques, regular maintenance

issues.title: Seat Memory Function Malfunctions
issues.description: Some owners experience issues with seat memory settings not saving properly or seats moving to incorrect positions when different driver profiles are selected.
issues.fix_description: System reset, motor replacement, or control module reprogramming
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of controls, avoid overloading memory functions

editorial.hero_blurb: The GX 550 trades its legendary V8 for a sophisticated twin-turbo V6 that delivers more power while maintaining the rugged capability Lexus off-roaders demand. This isn't just luxury transportationâ€”it's a premium adventure machine built for those who refuse to choose between comfort and conquest.
editorial.essence: The 2024 GX 550 represents Lexus's boldest reimagining of the body-on-frame SUV formula, pairing modern forced-induction efficiency with old-school toughness. It's the rare luxury vehicle that can tackle the Rubicon Trail on Saturday and valet duty on Sunday with equal confidence.
editorial.heritage: Born from the legendary Land Cruiser Prado platform, the GX has been Lexus's answer to premium off-road capability since 2003. The 550 marks a new chapter, abandoning the beloved 4.6L V8 for turbocharged modernity while maintaining the rock-solid foundation that made its predecessors legendary.
editorial.design_philosophy: Designers sought to balance rugged functionality with contemporary luxury, creating a vehicle that looks equally at home at a country club or base camp. The angular, upright stance prioritizes visibility and capability over aerodynamic efficiency, staying true to the GX's utilitarian roots.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a direct racing pedigree, the GX shares DNA with Toyota's Dakar Rally-winning vehicles and leverages decades of Land Cruiser engineering proven in the world's harshest environments from Australian Outback to African safari.
editorial.engine_character: The 3.4L twin-turbo V6 delivers immediate, linear power with surprising smoothness for a forced-induction unit. It feels muscular and responsive, building torque from low RPMs with a refined urgency that masks its considerable capability until you need every bit of its 349 horsepower.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 10-speed automatic operates with the deliberate precision of a luxury SUV, offering smooth shifts in comfort mode and more aggressive behavior when terrain or driving demands it. Manual control feels intuitive, with logical gear selection that complements the engine's torque curve.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Built on a proper ladder frame with sophisticated suspension tuning, the GX 550 manages to feel planted and controlled on-road while maintaining the articulation and durability serious off-roading demands. It's surprisingly composed for such a tall, heavy vehicle.
editorial.steering_feel: Steering is appropriately weighted with decent feedback for a body-on-frame SUV, offering confidence-inspiring precision at highway speeds while remaining light enough for technical off-road maneuvering. It won't be mistaken for a sports car, but it never feels vague or disconnected.
editorial.brake_confidence: Powerful, progressive brakes with excellent pedal feel that inspire confidence whether hauling a trailer down mountain grades or navigating steep descents off-road. The system handles the GX's substantial mass with authority and provides reassuring stopping power in all conditions.
editorial.sound_signature: The twin-turbo V6 produces a sophisticated growl under acceleration, more refined than its V8 predecessor but still distinctly purposeful. Exhaust note is pleasantly muted at cruise but develops character when pushed, with subtle turbo whoosh adding modern appeal.
editorial.ideal_owner: Affluent adventurers who demand genuine capability without sacrificing luxury, outdoor enthusiasts who need to tow boats or trailers, and families seeking a premium SUV that can handle any terrain while delivering Lexus refinement and reliability.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking maximum fuel economy, urban dwellers who prioritize parking ease over capability, or those wanting the most cargo space per dollar. Also not ideal for buyers nostalgic for the outgoing V8's character.
editorial.buyers_summary: The GX 550 successfully modernizes the luxury off-road formula without losing its soul. While the twin-turbo V6 may lack the V8's romance, it delivers superior performance and efficiency in a package that remains uncompromisingly capable.
pros: Genuine off-road capability with luxury refinement
Powerful and efficient twin-turbo V6 engine
Excellent build quality and reliability reputation
cons: Premium fuel economy still trails competitors
Interior space compromised by body-on-frame design
Higher price point than unibody luxury SUVs
best_for: Serious off-road adventures with luxury comfort
Towing boats, trailers, or recreational vehicles
